    <note>Liu(2) Yanbi [12187] Wang Tinggui, WJ, 44.5b-7a. According to Wang(2) Tinggui [12158], WJ, 44.6b, Yanbi's elder brother's grandson, Dong [12192], and his son, Tingjian [12188], were both given titles in 1142 (when Yanbi died) on the basis of the yibiao of their affinal kin (yinjia), Wu(3) Chengxiang (assisting minister of state). The only chronologically logical state council Wu(3) was Wu(3) Juhou [1965], who ended his career in 1113 at the age of 77. Juhou's wife was Liu(2), daughter of Feng(4) Jing's [607] daughter, who was the wife of a Liu(2) Gao(2) [22357] (identified as jinshi, but may mean studying for degree since not in lists). His son-in-law was an unidentified Liu(2) Mengzhi (not in dataset). I assume that Gao was a lineage kin of a previous generation. The son-in-law may, or may not, be related since the affinal relationship that would be operative here would be a daughter married to the Wu(3) rather than a son married to the Wu(3). See Wang Tinggui, WJ, 44.6b and Ge Shengzhong, WJ, 12.14a. CBD, 5, 3966.</note>
